namedLocations.description: Arial, sometimes marketed as Arial MT, is a sans-serif typeface and computer font packaged with Microsoft Windows, other Microsoft software applications, Apple Mac OS X, and many PostScript computer printers. The typeface was designed in 1982 by Robin Nicholas and Patricia Saunders for Monotype Typography. Arial is also a typeface family comprising standard Arial (Arial Std) and variants, including Arial Black, Bold, Extra Bold, Condensed, Italic, Light, Medium, Monospaced, Narrow, and Rounded.

transcript.text: Hello, welcome to the on Print shop.
In this video we will walk you through the enhancements we have made in the Designer Studio in this release.
In version 11.2 we made enhancements to the design preview, calendar and photo book products, new version creation for art week and month layouts and many more.
Let us walk you through the enhancements 1 by 1.
Talking about the first feature, the admin and the customers can now see the 3D preview of the product design in real time within the designer studio.
The activation of 3D preview functionality has been moved to the studio settings.
The admin can now enable the 3D preview with just one setting and it will be available for some of the standard products in the studio with a mini window preview.
If the admin wants to offer a side by side view instead of the mini window, they just need to enable the Enable 3D Preview side by side setting.
The next functionality is the Product Design Review.
We are introducing the Product Design Preview feature in the Designer Studio to streamline the process of finalizing artwork for order fulfillment.
This page will showcase the blank image, print quality, text placeholders, and any skipped page warnings.
This enhancement enables your customers to review and verify their designs, making necessary adjustments before placing their orders.
When the option for Design Preview is set to PDF in the Studio settings, customers will have one button in the studio to download the PDF proof.
The next feature in the line is creation of a new version of Art Week and Month layouts.
With the Create New version added to the individual Art Layouts action button.
The admin will be able to create a new art layout by modifying the layout title, product type, specific product assignment, and the design in the designer studio.
Next is the addition of an AI Assistant in the studio to help the customers with improving the content.
With AI Assistant, the customers can rephrase the text selected, change the tone of voice to formal, creative, or professional, or even fix the spelling errors.
The next one is in the event background enhancement in the calendar product.
The event names configured in the calendar product will be displayed on a white background for better visibility and readability.
Using the enhanced functionality, images added to the product design can be enhanced by removing the unwanted background or even upscaling the quality of the image.
For the group of text elements added to the studio canvas, the admin as well as the customers can manage the spacing horizontally, vertically or tidy up spacing.
The distribute spacing feature will be available for more than two text elements selected.
Last but not least, the zoom functionality has been optimized by adding a zoom slider at the bottom of the screen and displaying it as per the product sizes.
So these were some of the enhancements we have brought to the Designer Studio in version 11.2.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on on printshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
